    "These researchers found a high probability (50% or higher) of AI generation on 66% of abstracts written by ChatGPT-3; only one of the original abstracts had a probability higher than 50%.",
    "It is of note, however, that the abstracts were generated using ChatGPT-3, which is currently outdated.",
    "In recent years, advancements in AI have led to the development of sophisticated language models capable of generating text that closely resembles human-written content.",
    "However, the suitability and integrity of such AI models, like GPT-4, for scientific writing, particularly in the field of psychology, remain unclear (Alkaissi & McFarlane, 2023).",
    "Additionally, there is currently a lack of research examining the use of AI models for writing school psychology papers, an area crucial to the work of trainers and researchers."
